                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d9">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">810.24/45: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Peru</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Dreyfus</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Lima</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1939-06-29T10:00:00-05:00"
                            >June 29, 1939—10 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received 11:32 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>51. In reply to Department’s telegram of June 23 [<hi rend="italic">27</hi>], 7
                    p.m. the Minister for Foreign Affairs after consulting President Benavides has
                    informed me that he agrees in principle with the objectives of the proposed
                    resolution and looks with favor to its enactment.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Dreyfus</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
